This pile of quick hacks sloppily rectilinearizes aurora forecast images from [1], which makes it easier to read for those outside of North America.

[1] https://www.swpc.noaa.gov/products/aurora-30-minute-forecast

# there's no need to re-generate this map every time, one is enough
./generate-map

wget https://services.swpc.noaa.gov/images/animations/ovation/north/latest.jpg
./rectilinearize latest.jpg

$VIEWER latest.jpg-rect.jpg
# or
./mark-locations latest.jpg-rect.jpg
$VIEWER latest.jpg-marked.jpg
